  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Consider the triangle with sides 6, 8 and 10. It can be seen that the perimeter and the area are both equal to 24.</p>\n<p>So the $\\frac{\\text{area}}{\\text{perimeter}}$ ratio is equal to 1.</p>\n<p>Consider also the triangle with sides 13, 14 and 15. The perimeter equals 42 while the area is equal to 84.</p>\n<p>So for this triangle the $\\frac{\\text{area}}{\\text{perimeter}}$ ratio is equal to 2.</p>\n<p>Find the sum of the perimeters of all integer sided triangles for which the area/perimeter ratios are equal to positive integers not exceeding 1000.</p>\n</section>",
